1
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,780
Please have a seat.

2
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,520
Pour a glass of water for Miss Qin.

3
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,120
Yes, sir.

4
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,360
Mr. Matsuda.

5
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,039
Is this house arrest?

6
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,000
Miss Qin.

7
00:01:58,479 --> 00:02:00,680
Where are your harmonica team members?

8
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,400
Mr. Matsuda.

9
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,100
They can't take any more torment.

10
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,680
They are all citizens of Manchukuo.

11
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,320
Before,

12
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,340
they played the harmonica

13
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:19,079
to promote anti-Manchukuo and anti-Japanese sentiments.

14
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:21,680
I had to punish them slightly.

15
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,520
It was my last resort.

16
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,440
Since I let them go,

17
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,000
I won't go after them again.

18
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,840
But you, Miss Qin,

19
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,400
broke your promise

20
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,180
and went back on your word.

21
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,480
You caused a lot of trouble

22
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,000
for tomorrow's concert.

23
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,840
What I promised you,

24
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,530
I will definitely accomplish.

25
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:12,850
What do you mean?

26
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:14,840
Mr. Matsuda,

27
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,160
don't you appreciate my skills?

28
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,760
I alone

29
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:22,040
can play with the momentum of a whole band.

30
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,120
So you're saying

31
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,960
that tomorrow at the concert,

32
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,260
you'll perform

33
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,079
a harmonica solo?

34
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,560
Is that okay?

35
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,800
I look forward

36
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,120
to your performance at the concert

37
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,850
for the Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere.

38
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,050
See you tomorrow, Mr. Matsuda.

39
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,560
Take good care of Miss Qin.

40
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,080
Whatever she wants to eat or drink,

41
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:00,840
provide it immediately.

42
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,440
Yes, sir.

43
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,880
Without my order,

44
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,280
no one is allowed in.

45
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:04,920
Yes, sir.

46
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,280
Who is it?

47
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:25,840
Chen Yu.

48
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,080
Captain Matsuda sent me to bring Miss Qin her meal.

49
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:35,680
Please.

50
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,280
Miss Qin.

51
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,000
Mr. Matsuda sent me to ask

52
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,440
how the pieces for tomorrow's concert

53
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,440
are coming along.

54
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,560
'Kimigayo' and the national anthem of Manchukuo

55
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,090
have very simple melodies.

56
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,680
There is nothing to prepare.

57
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:06,920
That is good.

58
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,580
Enjoy your meal, Miss Qin.

59
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,480
Thank you, Chief Chen.

60
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,160
Please.

61
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,160
By the way.

62
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,800
If Miss Qin needs anything,

63
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,760
just let me know.

64
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:27,840
Goodbye.

65
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,159
Goodbye.

66
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:39,680
Chief Chen.

67
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,720
There is a famous harmonica piece,

68
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,800
'Battlefield Moon'.

69
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,930
Have you heard of it?

70
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,280
Remember.

71
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,360
If Sister Qin ever mentions 'Battlefield Moon' to you,

72
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,480
you must tell me.

73
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,560
'Battlefield Moon'.

74
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,480
This is the first time I've heard of it.

75
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:08,880
It's very beautiful. You should listen to it when you go back.

76
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:09,600
Okay.

77
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,800
Tomorrow, I will personally be in charge of

78
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,200
Miss Qin's security.

79
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:16,420
I will be listening attentively from the audience.

80
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,280
Goodbye.

81
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,440
Improvised segments cannot exceed 30 seconds,

82
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,240
for Shen Ling to decode quickly.

83
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,680
Five Races Under One Union, The Kingly Way and the Happy Land.

84
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,480
Officers of the Imperial Army,

85
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,159
elites of Manchukuo,

86
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:00,960
and ladies and gentlemen in attendance,

87
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,520
good evening.

88
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:13,120
Five Races Under One Union, The Kingly Way and the Happy Land.

89
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,400
The Manchukuo Harbin Concert

90
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,480
starts now.

91
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:24,280
Harbin is shining with stars tonight.

92
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:25,920
Lingzi.

93
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,340
Qin Na will pass the intelligence

94
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,200
during the improvised section.

95
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,240
As soon as she finishes sending the intelligence,

96
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,560
we will make our move.

97
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,320
It all depends on your signal.

98
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,040
Okay.

99
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,040
Once Sister Qin finishes sending the intelligence,

100
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:38,920
I will stand up.

101
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,000
Then you can make your move.

102
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:45,159
Now, let us use our most sincere feelings

103
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,880
to open this musical feast of Manchukuo

104
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,200
and the Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere.

105
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,520
First, we would like to invite

106
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:56,120
Miss Qin Na from the Harbin Harmonica Society.

107
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,400
She will play

108
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:01,640
the 'National Anthem of Manchukuo' and 'Kimigayo' on the harmonica.

109
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,720
Please welcome Miss Qin Na.

110
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,840
Before I play "Kimigayo"

111
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,970
and the "Manchukuo National Anthem",

112
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:36,400
I will first play a military song for everyone.

113
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,539
A military song? From which unit?

114
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:41,960
It sounds like the Kwantung Army's military song.

115
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,360
This girl

116
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,930
really knows the rules.

117
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,080
Lingzi.

118
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:21,760
Remember the basic rules we agreed on before.

119
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,840
Each intelligence category

120
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,100
is transmitted using two to three notes.

121
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:12,960
Suo Brigade.

122
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,540
One cavalry regiment.

123
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,960
Two infantry regiments.

124
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,600
Light weapons,

125
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,960
Type 38 rifles.

126
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,320
Three.

127
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,320
Heavy mortars.

128
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,480
One.

129
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,530
What is this melody?

130
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,930
Mr. Matsuda.

131
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,160
This is not the military song of our Kwantung Army.

132
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:50,040
Although the melody is somewhat passionate,

133
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,960
it is different from the Kwantung Army's military song.

134
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,020
Instead, it has a profound strength.

135
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,850
Especially those fluctuating melodies,

136
00:10:57,160 --> 00:11:00,560
yet exceptionally prominent high notes and articulations.

137
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,380
One grenade launcher.

138
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,100
Departure direction:

139
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:07,920
Tonghua,

140
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,000
Mengjiang,

141
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,290
advancing in multiple routes.

142
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,120
Stop.

143
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,360
What melody are you playing?

144
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,240
Combined attack convergence.

145
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,440
You are transmitting information.

146
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,840
Block all exits.

147
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,400
Catch the suspects.

148
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,680
Don't rush.

149
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,160
Arrest her.

150
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:46,320
Action.

151
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:48,960
Matsuda.

152
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,920
I will not let you catch me.
